<TITLE> Blackouts hit much of the country </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  Much of the country is reeling from power failures as the national grid has run into technical glitches, an official with Bangladesh Power Development Board said Saturday. ASM Bazlul Haque, director (public relations) of BPDB, told bdnews24.com at 1:40pm: "Repair work is going on. The situation will come back to normal within one hour." The power failures stemmed from the technical glitches at Ashuganj Power Station, which occurred at 11:45am. bdnews2
